Too bad you're leaving, guys.  There is still much to contribute.  Take a night to think about a different direction.  I've started a new thread, and maybe you could help there.  <br><br>
Right now, you guys are like the officer who happened to be a jet navigator who was on my team at Fairchild Air Force Base's Global Survival School.  We were told to complete a compass course, and given a map and the compass coordinates.  We got to a really thick brushy, marshy area, and the officer started going right straight through the bad stuff.  I told him we could go up the hill, get out of the marsh and brush, and simply walk around, but he insisted on going right straight through.  So a couple of buddies and I walked up the hill, around this undergrowth and to a point we had identified from the compass heading, and met him there.  It gave us a good laugh and a break besides.<br><br>
Enjoy the hiking.
